Home Properties, Fortune Brands Home to Join S&P MidCap 400

-- B y   J o a n n a   O s s i n g e r
-- 
2011-09-26T21:38:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/home-properties-fortune-brands-home-to-join-s-p-midcap-400.html
Home Properties Inc. (HME)  and Fortune
Brands Home & Security Inc. will join the Standard & Poor’s
MidCap 400 Index, S&P said in a statement today.  Home Properties will move to the midcap gauge from the S&P
SmallCap 600 Index after the close of trading on Sept. 30 to
replace  BJ’s Wholesale Club Inc. (BJ) , which is being bought by
Leonard Green & Partners LP and  CVC Capital Partners , S&P said.
Resources Connection Inc. will join the small-cap index at that
time as well.  Fortune Brands Home & Security will join the S&P MidCap 400
after the close of trading on Oct. 3, S&P said, replacing
 Overseas Shipholding Group Inc. (OSG) , which will be added to the S&P
SmallCap 600.  Measurement Specialties Inc. (MEAS)  will also be added to
the small-cap gauge at that time, and LCA-Vision and MedCath
will be deleted from it.  Fortune Brands, which is changing its name to Beam Inc.
after spinning off Fortune Brands Home & Security, will remain
in the  S&P 500 Index , S&P said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joanna Ossinger at 
 jossinger@bloomberg.net  